{{italic title}}
'''''Current Medical Diagnosis and Treatment''''' is a standard medical reference work<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Kim|first=E. Edmund|date=2009-01-01|title=Current Medical Diagnosis and Treatment|url=http://jnm.snmjournals.org/content/50/1/165|journal=Journal of Nuclear Medicine|language=en|volume=50|issue=1|pages=165–165|doi=10.2967/jnumed.108.056002|issn=0161-5505}}</ref> published by [[McGraw-Hill]].  It is updated annually and the 2017 version was its 56th edition.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=2Z_RDAAAQBAJ&q=current+medical+diagnosis+and+treatment&dq=current+medical+diagnosis+and+treatment&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiNvo_A7fDVAhVqAcAKHV2TA3UQ6AEIKDAA|title=CURRENT Medical Diagnosis and Treatment 2017|last=Papadakis|first=Maxine A.|last2=McPhee|first2=Stephen J.|last3=Rabow|first3=Michael W.|date=2016-09-05|publisher=McGraw Hill Professional|isbn=9781259585128|language=en}}</ref> The editors of the 55th edition were Stephen McPhee, Maxine Papadakis and Michael Rabow.  It was originally published as a general work, but a number of specialist versions have since been released, such as [[pediatrics]], [[cardiology]], and [[surgery]] as part of the Lange "Current" series.

