'''James Elkins''' (born 1955) is an American [[art historian]] and [[art critic]]. He is E.C. Chadbourne Chair of art history, theory, and criticism at the [[School of the Art Institute of Chicago]].<ref name=reviewersbookwatch/> He also coordinates the Stone Summer Theory Institute, a short term school on contemporary art history based at the [[School of the Art Institute of Chicago]].
==Education== *BA, cum laude, 1977, [[Cornell University]] *MFA and MA, 1983, and PhD with honors, 1989, [[University of Chicago]]
==Publications== *Pictures and Tears: A History of People Who Have Cried in Front of Paintings<ref>{{cite news |title=Stealing beauty |url=https://www.theguardian.com/Archive/Article/0,4273,4397376,00.html |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=April 20, 2002 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 | location=London | first=Alfred | last=Hickling}}</ref> *Chinese Landscape Painting as Western Art History *Pictures of the Body: Pain and Metamorphosis *The Domain of Images *How to Use Your Eyes<ref>{{cite news |title=Wait a minute - did you really see that? |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-67433633.html |work=[[The Christian Science Monitor]] |date=November 30, 2000 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref> *What Painting Is<ref>{{cite news |title=Dental Floss Alchemist |url=http://www.houstonpress.com/2001-04-05/culture/dental-floss-alchemist/ |work=[[Houston Press]] |date=April 5, 2001 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref> *The Poetics of Perspective *The Object Stares Back: On the Nature of Seeing<ref>{{cite news |title=Elegant vision of eye-mind concepts |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-56824510.html |work=[[The Washington Times]] |date=March 17, 1996 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref> *Why are our Pictures Puzzles?<ref name=artjournal/> *What Happened to Art Criticism?<ref>{{cite news |title=There goes the judge in today's art criticism, Critic urges peers to be better before the skill dies |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-7658603_ITM |work=[[Philadelphia Inquirer]] |date=April 7, 2004 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 | first=Carlin | last=Romano}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://observer.com/2004/09/art-criticism-in-crisis-james-elkins-studies-the-evidence/|title=Art Criticism in Crisis? James Elkins Studies the Evidence|last=Naves|first=Mario|date=September 13, 2004|website=Observer|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref> *Visual Studies: A Skeptical Introduction *Why Art Cannot Be Taught: A Handbook For Art Students<ref>{{cite news |title=Why Art Cannot Be Taught: A Handbook for Art Students.(Review) |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-10640868_ITM |work=[[Publishers Weekly]] |date=June 4, 2001 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref> *Six Stories From the End of Representation *Stories of Art<ref>{{cite news |title=Artworks Feature: EH Gombrich - Changing the Way We See |url=http://www.abc.net.au/rn/artworks/stories/2008/2245331.htm |work=[[Radio National]] |date=July 6, 2008 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref> *On the Strange Place of Religion in Contemporary Art<ref>{{cite news |title=On the Strange Place of Religion in Contemporary Art (Book Review) |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-1069809_ITM |work=Wisconsin Bookwatch |publisher=[[Midwest Book Review]] |date=November 1, 2004 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref> *On Pictures and the Words That Fail Them<ref name=artjournal>{{cite news |title=Close Reading and Looking: Some Recent Books by James Elkins (Review) |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-28171699_ITM |work=[[Art Journal (CAA)|Art Journal]] |date=June 22, 2000 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref> *Our Beautiful, Dry, and Distant Texts: Art History as Writing<ref name=artjournal/> *Master Narratives and Their Discontents<ref name=reviewersbookwatch>{{cite news |title=Master Narratives and Their Discontents (Book Review) |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-9725087_ITM |work=Reviewer's Bookwatch |publisher=[[Midwest Book Review]] |date=October 1, 2005 |accessdate=May 13, 2009 }}</ref>
